      },
      {
        "label": "The combination of apple and celery works. A tart green apple sorbet is not going to knock your socks",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "off, because you are programmed to know it. When you add the flavor of celery, you get something new. I",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "also love the flavors of apple and fennel together, especially in sorbet.",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "I make an apple confit of thinly sliced apples with cinnamon caramel powder layered between the apples",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "and baked slowly. When the dish is served, next to the apples is a small pile of dates poached in syrup",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "with vanilla. The other flavors on the plate are lemon confit, quince, raw apple with apple cider gelée",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "and ras el hanout (a Moroccan spice blend).",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "For this dish you need a contrast for the sweetness, so the role of the lemon confit is to cleanse and",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "refresh. If the confit was not there, you would have a bite of the sweet date and be done. The date and",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "lemon is like a salad. The line drawing this together is the quince and dates that come from the Middle",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "East and that was the line to ras el hanout .",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "If you cook apples on top of the stove, some varieties will have a lot of juice while others will have none",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "at all. Fuji, Gala, and Golden Delicious apples tend to be juicy, while Granny Smith apples are often",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "drier. With different types of apples, you often don’t know exactly what they will do. So if I’m going to",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "serve apples with gingerbread, I will sauté them in a little sugar and see what happens. If they are letting",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "out a bunch of juice, I won’t add much sugar. If they are dry, I’ll add some apple juice or Calvados.",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "When I make an apple pie, I won’t use any fewer than three different kinds of apples for their different",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "textures and sweetnesses, which ensures that every single bite is interesting. I’ll use Galas or Golden",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "Delicious apples for their sweetness in the middle of the pie, and soft Jonathans or McIntoshes on top for",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "their ability to melt into the others, and Braeburns or Granny Smiths on the bottom for their ability to stay",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "firm. . . . I can’t imagine an apple pie without cinnamon, a splash of lemon juice, and a pinch of salt.",
        "strength": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "Apples and caramel are a wonderful combination and depending on what nut you add it will take the",
        "strength": 2
      },
